Package org.panthercode.arctic.core.processing.modules

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Module
    A module is the basic unit for execution.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractModule
    The Abstract Module class is the root element in inheritance hierarchy.
    Bundle
    The bundle class is used to hold and proceed a list of modules.
    Chunk
    The Chunk class runs all elements parallelised.
    Counter
    The Counter class repeats the module's functionality until a numeric limit is reached or (if canAbort flag is set) until the module finished successfully.
    Loop
    Class to repeat module's functionality.
    Process
    The Process class runs one element after another.
    Repeater
    The Repeater repeats the module's functionality until the time limit is reached or until the module finished successfully.
    Step
    The step class is used to execute client code.
